HEADWORD: Cycas
<hw>Cy"cas</hw> <pr>(s?"k?s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of uncertain
origin. Linn⟦ae⟧us derives it from one of the ⟦ldquo⟧obscure Greek
words.⟦rdquo⟧]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of trees,
intermediate in character between the palms and the pines. The pith of
the trunk of some species furnishes a valuable kind of sago.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

